# erwinlares-site

Personal website for Erwin Lares, built with Quarto and deployed to Netlify via GitHub. The site lives at [erwinlares.com](https://erwinlares.com) and serves as the canonical hub in a hub-and-spoke publishing system — content written here propagates outward to a set of spoke platforms through an R-based dispatch layer.

---

## Architecture

The site is a static Quarto website, version-controlled in this repo (`erwinlares/erwinlares-site`) and deployed automatically by Netlify on every push to `main`. The hub-and-spoke model works as follows: every post lives here first, tagged and routed in its YAML front matter. Running `publish()` from the R console dispatches each post to whichever spoke platforms its front matter specifies — no manual copying, no per-platform reformatting.

The spokes are:

| Platform | URL | Dispatch method |
|---|---|---|
| erwinlares.com | erwinlares.com | git push → Netlify rebuild |
| BRUG (the-burrows) | github.com/erwinlares/the-burrows | GitHub Contents API |
| Las Rubieras Pottery | lasrubieraspottery.com | Shopify API (stub) |
| Aikido of Wisconsin | aikidoofwisconsin.com | — (Squarespace ruled out; migration pending) |
| RCI / UW–Madison | researchci.doit.wisc.edu | WordPress REST API (stub) |

Squarespace has no content-posting endpoints — its API is commerce-only — so it is permanently ruled out as a dispatch target. The aikido site is being migrated to its own Quarto + Netlify stack.

---

## Stack

- **Quarto** — site framework and rendering
- **R** — dispatch layer, `init_post()`, post-render hooks
- **GitHub** — version control; also the delivery mechanism for BRUG posts via the Contents API
- **Netlify** — hosting and continuous deployment
- **httr2** — HTTP requests in the dispatch layer
- **Bootswatch Lux** — base theme

The build is configured in `netlify.toml`. Netlify requires a custom `install_quarto.sh` script (see Troubleshooting).

