## Credentials and environment setup

All platform credentials live in `.Renviron` at the project root and are never committed to version control. `.Renviron` is listed in `.gitignore`.

On a fresh clone or new machine, create `.Renviron` and populate it with:

```
GITHUB_PAT_BRUG=ghp_...
```

`GITHUB_PAT_BRUG` is a fine-grained GitHub personal access token scoped to the `the-burrows` repo with **Contents: Read and Write** permission only. No other scopes are needed. Generate or regenerate it at GitHub → Settings → Developer settings → Fine-grained tokens.

As additional dispatch stubs are implemented, their credentials will live here too (Shopify API key, WordPress application password, etc.). The pattern is always the same: token in `.Renviron`, read in the dispatch function via `Sys.getenv()`, never hardcoded.

