## Troubleshooting / known quirks

**Netlify won't install Quarto via env var alone.** Setting `QUARTO_VERSION` in the Netlify environment is not sufficient — Netlify will not install Quarto from it. The repo includes `install_quarto.sh`, which downloads and extracts the Quarto binary to `$HOME` (not `/opt`, which requires permissions the build environment doesn't have). This script must be present and referenced in `netlify.toml`.

**CSS floats are unreliable in Quarto.** Quarto's layout system interferes with float-based CSS. If you need a photo or element to sit alongside text, use CSS Grid explicitly. The About page photo layout uses two HTML blocks — a grid div for the image-plus-first-paragraphs section, and a separate full-width div for the remainder — with sizing handled via inline styles to prevent Quarto from overriding them.

**Raw HTML inside Quarto div fences requires a raw block.** HTML inside `:::{}` divs must be wrapped in ` ```{=html} ` blocks, not written as bare HTML. Bare HTML inside a div fence will not render.

**Quarto listing `contents` needs a glob pattern for nested posts.** The listing that drives the journal feed uses `contents: ../posts/*/index.qmd`, not just `contents: ../posts`. The simpler path does not recurse into subdirectories. Similarly, the category filter requires a plain string (`categories: "journal"`), not array syntax.

**Quarto rewrites internal `.qmd` links to `.html` at render time.** Use `.qmd` paths when linking between pages in source — Quarto handles the `.html` translation. Writing `.html` paths in source will produce broken links in the editor and may cause issues if the rendering target changes.

**PR templates only auto-load from the root `.github/` directory.** The pull request template must live at `.github/pull_request_template.md` directly, not in any subfolder. GitHub will not auto-load it from a subdirectory.

**Favicons are aggressively cached.** After updating `favicon.svg`, do a hard browser refresh (`Cmd+Shift+R` / `Ctrl+Shift+R`) before concluding the favicon isn't working.